[{"id":"FT561949","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<u>Image 1</u> best illustrates which of the following broad economic transformations in the period circa 1750 ?","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"The figure presents a photograph titled &quot;Coal Mine in the English Midlands, circa 1750.&quot; On the left side of the photograph is a factory building. There is a man in the bottom left-hand corner pushing a full wheelbarrow. In the middle foreground of the photograph, there is a man leading two donkeys who are carrying full baskets on their backs. Behind the donkeys there is a man with a whip and a horse pulling a full carriage. In the right-hand corner there are men digging. A large tower is shown in the background with smoke coming out of it. To the right of the tower, a man is tending to a machine containing a mechanical pump. \" height=\"518\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/3c0234f907e77e4ce7a7fc736a3ce115/original.jpg\" width=\"687\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"The figure presents a photograph titled “Coal-Sifting Room at a Mine, Western France, circa 1850.” The photograph shows many men and women at work sifting coal in a mine. The photograph also shows a large machine consisting of a series of drums for crushing coal and pistons and a mechanical pulley system attached to the machine and various parts throughout the mine. \" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/e4e00bacad0d650342fafdb216d2f4d1/original.jpg\"></p>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p>The transition from an industrial to a postindustrial economy</p>","<p>The transition from a human- and animal-powered economy to a fossil-fuel economy</p>","<p>The transition from the First Industrial Revolution to the Second Industrial Revolution</p>","<p>The transition from guild-system manufacturing to putting-out-system manufacturing</p>"],"answer":0}]